-- Draghi Urges Global Supervision for Financial Firms, Washington Post Says
-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 2010-10-11T07:34:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/draghi-urges-global-supervision-for-financial-firms-washington-post-says.html
Financial companies that are “too
big to fail” should be subject to supervision at a global
level, said Mario Draghi, who heads Italy’s central bank and the
Financial Stability Board, an international panel working on
regulatory reform.  The board has yet to work out details, but a general set of
16 recommendations will be presented at a gathering of world
leaders next month in Seoul, the newspaper said.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
